name: NSApplicationDelegate
desc: A set of methods that delegates of NSApplication objects can implement.

items.name: applicationWillFinishLaunching
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately before the application object is initialized.

items.name: applicationDidFinishLaunching
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center after the application has been launched and initialized but before it has received its first event.

items.name: applicationWillBecomeActive
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately before the application becomes active.

items.name: applicationDidBecomeActive
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately after the application becomes active.

items.name: applicationWillResignActive
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately before the application is deactivated.

items.name: applicationDidResignActive
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately after the application is deactivated.

items.name: applicationShouldTerminate
items.desc: Sent to notify the delegate that the application is about to terminate.

items.name: applicationShouldTerminateAfterLastWindowClosed
items.desc: Invoked when the user closes the last window the application has open.

items.name: applicationWillTerminate
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately before the application terminates.

items.name: NSApplication.TerminateReply
items.desc: Constants used by the delegate method applicationShouldTerminate(_:) to determine whether an app should terminate.

items.name: applicationWillHide
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately before the application is hidden.

items.name: applicationDidHide
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately after the application is hidden.

items.name: applicationWillUnhide
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately after the application is unhidden.

items.name: applicationDidUnhide
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately after the application is made visible.

items.name: applicationWillUpdate
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately before the application object updates its windows.

items.name: applicationDidUpdate
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center immediately after the application object updates its windows.

items.name: applicationShouldHandleReopen
items.desc: Sent by the application to the delegate prior to default behavior to reopen (rapp) AppleEvents.

items.name: applicationDockMenu
items.desc: Allows the delegate to supply a dock menu for the application dynamically.

items.name: application
items.desc: Sent to the delegate before the specified application presents an error message to the user.

items.name: applicationDidChangeScreenParameters
items.desc: Sent by the default notification center when the configuration of the displays attached to the computer is changed (either programmatically or when the user changes settings in the Displays control panel).

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate the user wants to continue an activity in your app.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate that the activity could not be continued.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate that the user activity object has been updated.

items.name: application
items.desc: Sent to the delegate when Apple Push Services successfully completes the registration process.

items.name: application
items.desc: Sent to the delegate when Apple Push Service cannot successfully complete the registration process.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate that the user accepted a CloudKit sharing invitation associated with your app.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate to open a single file.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate to open a file programmatically.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate to open a temporary file.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate to open multiple files.

items.name: applicationOpenUntitledFile
items.desc: Tells the delegate to open an untitled file.

items.name: applicationShouldOpenUntitledFile
items.desc: Invoked immediately before opening an untitled file.

items.name: application
items.desc: Sent when the user starts up the application on the command line with the -NSPrint option.

items.name: NSApplication.PrintReply
items.desc: Constants that are returned by the delegate method application(_:printFiles:withSettings:showPrintPanels:).

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate the application has extracted its restorable state from a given archiver.

items.name: application
items.desc: Tells the delegate the application will encode any application state that was preserved between application launches.

items.name: applicationDidChangeOcclusionState
items.desc: Tells the delegate the applicationâ€™s occlusion state changed.

items.name: application
items.desc: Returns a Boolean value indicating whether the delegate can handle operations on the specified key-value key.
